              <code class="mono">capgo build request --platform ios</code> archives, signs and uploads to TestFlight. <code class="mono">--platform android</code> assembles, signs with
              your keystore and uploads to Play. One CLI, identical UX.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tile" data-expandable data-accent="yellow">
            <span class="icon"
              ><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"
                ><rect x="7" y="7" width="10" height="10" rx="1.5"></rect><path d="M10 7V4M14 7V4M10 20v-3M14 20v-3M7 10H4M7 14H4M20 10h-3M20 14h-3"></path></svg
              ></span
            >
            <h3 class="ttl"><span class="ttl-accent">{copy('native_build_v2_tile_hw_title')}</span></h3>
            <p class="sub">{copy('native_build_v2_tile_hw_sub')}</p>
            <div class="more">iOS and Android jobs run on M4 Mac runners with fast Xcode, Gradle, and Fastlane. You don't pick the runner; we do, by platform flag.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="tile" data-expandable data-accent="green">
            <span class="icon"
              ><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"
